Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @Olive Oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, sprinkle over the @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}. Drain the @Burrata{125%grams}.

Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

When the potatoes have 15 mins left, pop your @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} onto the same #tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Return to the oven for ~{3-4%minutes}.

The broccoli will finish cooking later on the naanizzas.

In the meantime, pop the @Plain Naans{2} onto a baking tray.

Divide the @Marinara Sauce{120%grams} between them and spread with the back of a #spoon{}, leaving a 1cm border. Sprinkle over the cheese.

Once the broccoli is slightly tender, remove them from the oven and arrange over the naans. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Bake on the top shelf until the cheese is melted and the broccoli are tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While everything's in the oven, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @Fresh Pesto{32%grams} and @Olive Oil{2%tbsp}.

Transfer the naanizzas to your plates, halve the burrata and place one half on the centre of each.

Drizzle over the pesto and serve with your herby potatoes alongside.

Enjoy!